race.comment: SUPER QUICK (2) showed good early dash and held on well to finish 3 lengths back in third over 1200m at Doomben. Was a comfortable all-the-way winner at Ipswich prior. Will enjoy a drop in class and from a low gate he can bounce back. THAT'S AN EXTRA (8) is in the hot Pat Webster yard and brings a win and a placing in this grade from Toowoomba. Has been kept on the fresh side and is a decent hope. TAVIS TOWN (6) resumed improved at the Sunshine Coast and Wiggins stays aboard. Proven second-up and he can show more like his best this preparation. RUSSIAN SUB (1) is third up and should be ready to feature. He has plenty up his sleeve and is well placed at best with a 3kg claimer aboard. The gate is tricky.
